This name is also a variant of   Wight  . The surname <i>White</i> is also very common among African Americans.","Irish and Scottish: adopted for any of several Irish and Scottish Gaelic names based on <i>bán</i> ‘white, fair’ (see   Bain   1,   McElwain  ) or <i>fionn</i> ‘fair’ (see   Finn   1). The English surname has been Gaelicized in Ireland as <b>de Faoite</b>.","Americanized form (translation into English) of various European surnames meaning ‘white’, for example German   Weiss  , French   Blanc  , Polish <b>Białas</b> (see   Bialas  ), Slovenian   Belec  , or any other synonymous Slavic surname beginning with <i>Bel-</i>, <i>Bev-</i>, <i>Biel-</i> or <i>Bil-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Mr","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maureen   and, less commonly, of   Maurice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mr Whyte was born about 1480, in Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland. He had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Mrs Whyte."},"et":{"about 1480–":"umbes 1480–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1500–Female":"1500–Surnud","1516–1564":"1516–1564","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1500":"1500","1564":"1564","about 1500":"umbes 1500","1480":"1480","ABT 1516":"umbes 1516","1516":"1516","Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland":"Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland","Of, Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland":"Dunfermline, Fife, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1480–":"noin 1480–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1500–Female":"1500–Kuollut","1516–1564":"1516–1564","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","1500":"1500","1564":"1564","about 1500":"noin 1500","1480":"1480","ABT 1516":"noin 1516","1516":"1516","Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland":"Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland","Of, Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland":"Dunfermline, Fife, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1480–":"environ 1480–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1500–Female":"1500–Décédée","1516–1564":"1516–1564","1480–Male":"1480–Décéd